DNC later joined the [[Communist Party of India]], then [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]] (CPI(M)) and then [[Communist Party of India (Marxist-Leninist)]] (CPI(ML)). The group was led by [[Ram Piara Saraf]].<ref>Mohanty, Manoranjan. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=da2NAAAAMAAJ Revolutionary Violence. A Study of the Maoist Movement in India]''. [[New Delhi]]: Sterling Publishers, 1977. p. 106-107.</ref>

